      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are a debated topic because they can have both intended and unintended consequences. Proponents argue they shield local industries from cheaper foreign competition, allowing domestic businesses to grow and maintain jobs. However, critics point out that tariffs often lead to higher prices for consumers, as the cost of the tariff is usually passed down to the buyer. Ultimately, the effect depends on the specific industry and how the trade policy is implemented.",
